@NODE ohis "Old History"

Version 0.5b  - First release.
              - Sysop function beta test release. Released to 1 sysop only.

Version 0.6b  - Now prints area and CD list in 1 column if less than 21
                areas/CD's.
              - Fixed a problem with area deletion.
              - Changed sysop edit menu.
              - Now calls sysop menu from user menu.
              - Allows listing of areas from sysop menu.
              - Completed all but the tagging and file moving routines.
              - Fixed a problem with locating correct data elements.
              - Fixed a problem when deleting/editing a file.

Version 0.7b  - Added partial List/Tag option.
              - Added user stats command.

Version 0.8b  - Second release.
              - Completed tag routines.
              - Added on-line help file.
              - Re-coded some areas to save a few bytes on EXE size.

Version 0.9b  - Third release. First worldwide release.
              - Fixed a problem when changing CD's on a single drive system.
              - Fixed a perceived bug of edited area data not being updated
                until exit. It was, but was not being read back in to the
                area list string.
              - Added configurable copy path.
              - Added checking for batch protocol when using external path.

Version 0.95b - Added download count incrementing.
              - Fixed a fatal bug when a file already existed in an alternate
                copy path.
              - Now runs in full user mode with keyfile checking.

Version 0.96  - Fixed a 90 byte memory leak when a tagged file already existed
                in the destination directory.
              - Added report file and errors file.
              - Now handles 'end of file' errors with a requestor.
              - Now displays correct CD number.
              - Fixed a bug which caused files copied to USER: not to be
                installed as standard issue DLG files. (Mis-spelled
                variable!)
              - Added configurable language's for most text output
              - Added configurable languages for help file.
              - Fixed a bug where garbage was displayed when changing areas
                after changing CD's and there was no CD change.
              - Fixed a bug which caused the free flag to be wrong.
              - Now handles multi-line FILES.BBS.
              - Now exits program if <RET> is pressed during area change and
                no area previously selected.

Version 0.97  - Added code to produce data file for BP
              - Added -M parameter.

Version 0.98  - Incorperated BP into Blitz-CD.
              - Added single area file search.
              - Fixed a bug in the language detection routine.
              - Added 'ConDir' environment variable support.

Version 0.98a - Really fixed the bug in the language detection routine!

Version 0.98b - Fixed a serious bug in end-of-file detection. Now should never
                get an 'end of file' error when reading in the 'FILES.BBS'
                style file.

Version 0.99  - Fixed a severe bug when empty search pattern entered.
              - Fixed a bug that would cause DLG to continually show the first
                file in the private area. This is caused when DLG encounters
                a low file pointer of 0 in the 'pointers.file' file.
              - Fixed a bug which would show garbage in the description of
                files copied to private area.
              - Now shows all CD's, marking existing ones with an asteric.
              - Will not allow users to tag files if they don't have a batch
                protocol selected and an alternate non-USER: path is in use.
              - Changed 'Thankyou' to 'Thank you' (Geez some are picky:-)
              - No longer allows non-sysops to enter sysop menu if they find
                the 'S' key.
              - Added mid access level.
              - Added the 9 description lines at top of config (begin with ';'
              - Added CD seperater line to config. Makes it easier to see
                where 1 CD ends and another begins.

Version 1.00  - Added -Z option.
              - Now prints 'Please wait ...' when loading in file list.
              - Now loads in the file list when entering the area, rather
                than when using F or L in that area for the first time.
              - Now copies files without protection bits. Apparantly some CD's
                have the protection bits set incorrectly, and Blitz-CD was
                failing.
              - Now looks for the .IDX file in RAM first.
              - Fixed a severe bug when 'Q)uit'ting out of a search.

Version 1.00a - Fixed a very nasty bug which caused non-registered users to
                have problems (including crashes).
              - Fixed a bug in detecting an empty area.

Version 1.01  - Fixed a bug that would allow users to select any CD number
                even if it wasn't listed.
              - Fixed a bug in the way protocols are detected and listed.
              - Moved the ratio detector further into the tag routine. Will
                now detect if the file already exists in batch list first.
              - Now only scans the users private directory when changing
                areas. This speeds up listing of areas.
              - Removed UPDATE parameter code. See appropriate section for
                details.

Version 1.02  - Fixed a bug in the ratio detector. This would cause a
                'Divide by zero' error for users who had not uploaded
                anything.
              - Added parameter: SHOWCD
              - Now checks for the specified language strings file, and if it
                can't find it, will then look for an English version of the
                strings.

Version 1.03  - Fixed a bug that would not pause the display in certain
                situations.
              - Added the number of files in area to main menu.

Version 1.04  - Fixed a bug that would prevent tagging on the last page of
                files in an area.
              - Fixed a bug when copying huge files.
              - Now uses DLG's FileCopy() function to copy files. This is a
                bit slower than the old way.
              - Now checks drive space before copying the file, and won't
                allow the copy if there isn't enough disk space.
              - Now falls back to default CD list if an alternate CD list
                can't be found.

Version 1.05  - Fixed a bug in the search option that would tag the wrong
                file.

Version 1.06b - Added true multi-line support!
              - Released to 1 sysop only.

Version 1.07b - Added multi-line to find option.
              - Now pre-processes each data file before working on them
                during import.

Version 1.08b - Minor changes.

Version 1.09b - Fixed a bug in copying files to private area.

Version 1.1b  - Now asks user to select area before listing areas.
              - Now the 1ONLY switch need not be used. Implemented dynamic
                tag blocking when copying files.
              - Changed the way files are copied.
              - Added optional logging.
              - Fixed upper case only when editing file area names.

Version 1.2b  - Fixed some bugs in the copy routine. This may have caused
                crashes in certain circumstances.
              - Fixed a bug in choosing CD routine. Users with access to NO
                CD's were causing the port to lock-up, as Blitz-CD didn't
                check for this situation (oops!).
              - Removed redundant line for header lines in 'Blitz-CD.List'
              - Shortened some parameter keywords.
              - Fixed up a bug in error trapping routine.
              - Fixed a major bug when copying to a non-USER: directory.
              - Fixed a bug which was causing the data files to become
                corrupt.
              - Tidied up a bug in the sysop edit menu.
              - Added a line to the language file!
              - Now only displays transfer information during start-up
                when the user doesn't have a batch protocol selected.
              - A number of little things spotted along the way were also
                fixed.
              - Added -K0 and -K1 switches.

Version 1.3b  - Fixed a bug which would cause the program to crash under
                certain conditions.
              - Fixed a bug when an error occured before jumping to the
                import routine.
              - Now correctly handles blank lines in the ASCII file list (the
                cause for bug #1 above!)

Version 1.4b  - Fixed a bug which would lock a port if the CD directory
                didn't exist.
              - Changed the way language strings are read.
              - Language file now conforms with language file rules of the
                M-Tag package!
              - Removed some un-used strings from the language file.
              - Fixed a bug in the operation of the '1ONLY' switch.

@ENDNODE
@NODE History " Blitz-CD history"

                See @{"Old History" link ohis} for version's prior to 1.5b.

Version 1.5b  - Fixed a bug which caused the last character to be cut from
                a description.
              - Made tag line prompt part of the language file.
              - Added SM option for sysop.
              - Made Blitz-CD also work as a demo in unregistered version.
              - Fixed a bug in custom language string handling which would
                cause strings with ,A appended to fail to be converted.
              - Can now use 'Blitz-CD:' as storage area rather than
                'FILE:Blitz-CD/'

Version 1.6b  - Changed where the [PRESS RETURN] is printed when loading an
                area.
              - Added the ability to assume CD is in drive.
              - Fixed a display bug when searching for files.
              - Fixed a bug which caused the wrong access levels and free
                flags to be used.
              - Added entire CD searching. HAPPY NOW!!
              - Included Italian language file.

Version 1.7b  - Now prints the current CD number and name on the main menu.
              - Now leaves the current area on-screen when doing a search.
              - Now uses a binary file for the CD list.
              - Included 'CD-Config' to create CD list's.
              - Fixed a bug that caused areas not to be listed correctly.
              - Fixed a bug that would cause Blitz-CD to crash in small areas.
              - Made the Failed Locks print the area number to make it easier
                to remove the data from the filelist.
              - Fixed a swag of enforcer hits when importing CD's. See the
                section on language files for details.
              - Removed the [PRESS RETURN] after loading in an area.
              - Now prints a 'Please wait ...' if more than 100 areas exist
                in the chosen CD.
              - Added some more strings to the language file.
              - Now has an abort key when doing CD searches.

Version 1.8b  - Fixed a bug in the read area routine which caused spurious
                crashes, although the crash should have ocured every time.
              - Made main menu commands configurable.
              - Fixed several small bugs in the area data file department.

Version 1.9b  - Due to popular demand, the need for CD-Config has been
                removed! Now the old ASCII file lists are back in use!
              - Added NODSIZE parameter.

Version 1.9bp1- Fixed a problem when changeing CD's.
              - Made CD selection more robust.

Version 1.9bp2- Should now correctly print a space after the CD list.
              - The EK switch now cuts in after 10 seconds.
              - A forced removal of the environment variable during dynamic
                tag blocking after 20 seconds.
              - NODSIZE now also prevents Blitz-CD from checking if the user
                has room in their private directory for the files.
              - Fixed some logic bugs when CD's were absent.

Version 2.0   - First full public release since v1.04!

@ENDNODE
